            <div class="paragraph col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2"><p>User interviews and a waste facility visit highlighted a variety of key insights. It is often both more convenient and cheaper to buy new furniture from retailers than it is to buy second hand or to try to repair damaged products. The most common reason for disposing of furniture was to change style, with only 15% due to an item being broken.</p></div>
